    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-01-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="736"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d736">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName type="from">Mavroyeni Bey</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to"
                            >Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial Legation of Turkey</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Imperial Legation of Turkey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-01-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: The Ottoman consul-general at
                    New York informs me that 30 Armenians, residing in New York, propose to engage
                    in military drill in order that, upon occasion, they may be prepared, as they
                    openly declare through their journals, to disturb order and tranquillity in
                    Turkey.</p>
                <p>Whatever may be the provisions of law in force in the United States, it is
                    evident that, in the case of a government, as in this instance, the competent
                    authorities of the State of New York are in a position to prevent these drills
                    whenever they take place. Therefore I pray your excellency to be pleased to send
                    a copy of my present note to them, in order that they may forthwith be advised
                    of the matter.</p>
                <p>Be pleased, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mavroyeni.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
